<HEADLINE>
<P>
LORENA BOBBITT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 We are hearing a lot of empty rhetoric about what the latest Bobbitt verdict 
really means ("Lorena Bobbitt Acquitted in Mutilation of Husband," Jan. 22). 
"Is it OK for women to cut off their husband's penis? Was it a feminist act?" 
What utter, bigoted nonsense! We didn't hear any such comments or posturing 
about the verdict in John Wayne Bobbitt's trial."Is it OK for a man to rape and 
batter his wife?" 
</P>
<P>
 I heard a lawyer, a woman, proclaim that all she had to do was leave. Easy for 
her to say. She had a prestigious legal career, money, full knowledge of the 
law and how to use the mighty power of the law to protect herself. These things 
are not commonly possessed by manicurists. 
</P>
<P>
 Blaming Lorena Bobbitt for her victimhood by saying she could just get out of 
the horrible situation she was living in by leaving her abusive husband is like 
saying that the abused and ghettoized poor victims of crime in our urban slums 
are really to blame for the high rate of murders, rapes, and robberies in their 
poverty-stricken neighborhoods because they obstinately refuse to move into the 
affluent suburbs. The jury heard all the evidence and couldn't find it in their 
hearts to convict her. They thought she was a little crazy. Isn't that enough? 
</P>
<P>
 J. L. PHILLIPS 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Beach 
</P>
<P>
 Considering the amount of abuse Lorena Bobbitt was subjected to during her 
marriage, I'd say she mutilated her husband while in a state of temporary 
sanity. 
</P>
<P>
 ALYSON ROSS 
</P>
<P>
 Alhambra 
</P>
<P>
 John Wayne Bobbitt was found innocent. Lorena Bobbitt was found not guilty. I 
guess, nothing ever happened then, huh? 
</P>
<P>
 EDGAR SOLLER 
</P>
<P>
 Fontana 
</P>
</TEXT>
