<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Martita Emde 
</P>
<P>
 Marina, Sr. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with a passing knowledge of the Marina girls' basketball team is aware 
of Shandy Robbins, who averaged 18 points and nine rebounds in the Vikings' 
Sunset League victories over No. 6 Ocean View, No. 7 Fountain Valley and 
Westminster.But although her stats aren't as impressive, Emde was no less 
important. Emde, who also is a defensive standout, scored 12 points in the 
48-45 victory over Ocean View, had 12 points and eight assists in a 59-47 
victory over Westminster and scored 17 -- 14 in the second half -- in a 49-43 
victory over Fountain Valley. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Jessica Eggleston and Julie Adams, Cypress, scored 31 and 27 points in an 
82-60 Empire League victory over second-place Katella. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kathy Peterson, Villa Park, scored in the Spartans' 1-0 upset of El Modena, 
then ranked fourth in the county in girls' soccer. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jamie Shine, El Modena, had 19 points and 14 rebounds in a 51-36 upset of 
10th-ranked Villa Park. 
</P>
<P>
 * Erin Stovall, Woodbridge, scored 23 points in a 77-27 victory over Santa 
Margarita and 20 in a 101-37 victory over Corona del Mar. 
</P>
