<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY-AREA DIGEST: HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three high school football All-Americans from the region are expected to 
participate in a large-scale ceremony Wednesday marking the NCAA's national 
letter-of-intent day. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Keith Smith and receiver Leodes Van Buren of Newbury Park and 
running back Tyrone Crenshaw of Sylmar are expected to sign their respective 
letters of intent along with several other Southland standouts at the 
headquarters of Bluechip Illustrated, a national recruiting magazine based in 
Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Other All-Americans expected to attend include Glenn Thompkins of Eisenhower, 
Rodney Sermons of Bishop Amat and Justin Stallings of Hawthorne. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith has committed to Arizona, Van Buren will sign with Colorado and Crenshaw 
has chosen Michigan State. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony will begin at 12:30 p.m. 
