<P>
 BLACK HISTORY: The city of Port Hueneme, which has the largest percentage of 
African Americans in Ventura County, has been hosting a photo exhibition 
depicting the history of the black community as a prelude to Black History 
Month. . . . "We've had a lot of people come in just to look at it," said Sara 
Ellinwood, of the Ray D. Prueter Library. . . . Black History Month starts 
today, and the library will display a collection of old photos from Oxnard 
resident Ira Mae Verrett. 
</P>
<P>
 DRY SPELL?: Weather watchers have marked the end of another month with 
below-average rainfall (B1), raising fears that the county may be entering 
another dry period. . . . Rainfall totals countywide measured only 36% of 
normal, and no rain is on the horizon at least through Sunday. "It's not as bad 
as the worst," state hydrologist Maurice Roos said, "but it would sure be nice 
if it were better." 
</P>
<P>
 RADAR WARS: Opponents of a microwave radar tower have taken their fight to the 
airwaves. Ojai residents, joined by Rep. Elton Gallegly, are scheduled to tape 
an episode of the "Montel Williams Show" today. . . . "We want no radiation 
without representation," said David Hedman, a spokesman for the group that has 
sued the federal government to prevent a 98-foot weather-tracking station from 
being switched on. . . . The daytime talk show apparently has found fertile 
ground in Ventura County. Williams did a segment last month on twin brothers 
from Oxnard who traded places in jail. 
</P>
<P>
 QUIET COMPETITION: Borla Performance Industries is making a lot of noise in 
the Japanese muffler market (Valley Business, Page 10). . . . The Oxnard 
company, which markets a line of stainless-steel exhaust systems, introduced 
its first product for the Japanese at a Tokyo auto show last month. . . . 
"We're riding the wave of American automobiles that are winding up in Japan," 
company President Alexander Borla said. African Americans 
</P>
<P>
 Percentage of blacks in Ventura County cities: Port Hueneme: 5.7% Oxnard: 5.3% 
Ventura: 1.7% Camarillo: 1.6% Simi Valley: 1.5% Thousand Oaks: 1.2% Moorpark: 
1.0% Ojai: 0.3% Fillmore: 0.2% Santa Paula: 0.1% Source: U.S. Census  
