<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPLOYMENT OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I am curious to know why your reporters consistently refer to the Employment 
Development Department as "the unemployment office."I find no rationale for it 
except that among the functions of the office is processing applications for 
unemployment insurance benefits. The primary purpose is, as its official name 
notes, development of employment opportunities. A person does not have to be 
unemployed to be served there. 
</P>
<P>
 Television reporters use the same designation. This conveys a negative image 
to the public and anyone who wants to use the services of that department.  
</P>
<P>
 RAY BRACY 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 
</P>
</TEXT>
