<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-CUB SMITH OKS ONE-YEAR DEAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While he doesn't have the glamour or magnetism of Bo Jackson, the Angels 
grabbed another candidate for their left field job Monday when they reached 
agreement with free agent Dwight Smith. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith will sign a one-year contract for about $700,000, according to sources, 
and be placed on the 40-man roster. The Angels are expected to make the 
announcement today. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, 30, batted .300 for the Cubs last season with a career-high 11 homer 
runs. Smith, runner-up for the 1989 National League rookie of the year award, 
holds the Cubs' all-time record with 50 pinch-hits in his five-year career. BOB 
NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
