<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
FIRM OFFERS FREE HOUSING TO ELDERLY QUAKE VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Costa Mesa-based company that provides assisted living to senior citizens 
announced Monday that it will provide free, temporary housing for elderly 
victims of the Northridge earthquake.  
</P>
<P>
 Seniors can choose a furnished unit at senior apartment communities owned by 
ARV Housing Group in Redondo Beach, Azusa, Pomona, Claremont, or at three 
retirement villas in Covina, San Dimas and Walnut, said company spokesman 
Bernard Sandalow.Housing is also available in Ontario. 
</P>
<P>
 Sandalow said the offer is good through March 1. Seniors will be accommodated 
on a first-come, first-served basis and will be under no obligation to buy or 
rent the facility in which they stay, he said. The program is being offered in 
cooperation with the Los Angeles chapter of the American Red Cross, Sandalow 
said. 
</P>
