<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; NEW YORK; TRADE CENTER JURY SEES CAPTURED VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The prosecution in the World Trade Center bombing case played a videotape 
seized from one of the defendants that showed commando-style raids, including 
the blowing up of a building with an American flag on top. The videotape was 
found with other bomb-making books and manuals in the suitcase of Ahmad Ajaj 
when he tried to enter the country with a fake Swedish passport in September, 
1992. He was serving a six-month prison sentence for illegally entering the 
country when the bomb went off Feb. 26, killing six people and injuring more 
than 1,000 at the world's largest office complex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
