<P>
IN BRIEF; PHOTOGRAPHY EXHIBIT DETAILS MOVIE PALACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A photographic exhibition featuring historic and contemporary images of 12 
Downtown Los Angeles movie palaces will be featured in the Grand Lobby of the 
Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences, 8949 Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills 
Saturday at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The Academy will also present "The Golden Era of the Movie Palace," a two-hour 
program of film clips, theatrical history and personal appearances by the 
people who brought the movie palaces to life. 
</P>
<P>
 For this presentation, tickets are $6 for the general public and $4 for 
academy members. 
</P>
<P>
 The exhibition will run through April 3 and is free to the public. Viewing 
hours are Tuesdays through Fridays, 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. and weekends, noon to 6 
p.m. For more information, call (310) 278-5673. 
