<TEXT>
<P>
 Unifrance Film President Apologizes: Daniel Toscan du Plantier says he is 
sorry for a "bad joke" attributed to him in which he was quoted as saying the 
earthquake in Los Angeles was God's retribution to Hollywood. In a letter to 
Motion Picture Assn. of America President Jack Valenti, Toscan du Plantier 
wrote, "I feel ashamed," and said he had made the remarks "among friends in a 
bar" in reference to the American versus French position on the audiovisual 
element of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. An angry Valenti last 
week wrote the Unifrance executive, saying the words had shocked and outraged 
him. 
