REGIONAL ROUNDUP: FORTUNE PETROLEUM BUYS INTO TEXAS GAS FIELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fortune Petroleum Corp. announced that it will acquire a 50% leasehold in the 
Brooklyn Union La Rosa natural gas field in Refugio County, Tex.Fortune will 
pay $750,000 for the lease from its $10-million line of credit extended by Bank 
One in Texas. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura Hills-based Fortune is an independent oil and gas exploration and 
production company. The company's principal properties are located in Texas and 
California. Fortune is in the midst of a multiyear plan to acquire natural gas 
producing properties. 
</P>
