<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: IWERKS TO BUILD SIMULATION THEATER AT SIX FLAGS PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burbank-based Iwerks Entertainment has signed an agreement with Six Flags 
Theme Parks to build a 100-seat simulation ride theater for the Six Flags park 
in Jackson, N.J. Iwerks said it will also produce a simulation film based on 
the movie "The Right Stuff," which will be seen in the theater. 
</P>
<P>
 Financial details of the deal were not released. Iwerks said it expected the 
theater to debut this spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Separately, the company said Eric G. Rodli will assume the role of chief 
operating officer in addition to his current position as chief financial 
officer. Iwerks, which went public last fall, is a supplier of special-format 
movie theaters, motion-simulation rides and virtual-reality games. 
