<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: WELLNESS FOUNDATION'S GRANT PROGRAM GROWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Wellness Foundation said it expects to give $30 million in 
grants to nonprofit organizations, double last year's amount, as a result of 
the just-completed merger of Woodland Hills-based Health Net and QualMed of 
Pueblo, Colo. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit foundation was created by law in 1992 when Health Net was 
converted from a nonprofit health maintenance organization to a for-profit HMO. 
</P>
