<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: FOOTHILL GROUP'S PROFITS FOR 4TH QUARTER SURGE 34% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Foothill Group, a financial services firm with headquarters in Agoura 
Hills and Los Angeles, said its fourth-quarter profit surged 34% to $3.53 
million, from $2.64 million a year earlier.The profit came despite a loss of 
$1.24 million from its thrift subsidiary, which Foothill spun off to its 
shareholders in December. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, the Foothill Group's profit climbed 55% to $18.7 million, 
from $12.1 million for 1992. Foothill attributed the better results to 
improvements in interest margins, growth of its asset-based loan portfolio and 
robust money management activities. Foothill said that at the end of 1993, it 
had total assets owned or under management of more than $1.1 billion. 
</P>
