<HEADLINE>
<P>
INFLATION RATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I am appalled by the use of the word only to describe the 2.7% rate of 
inflation for 1993 (Jan. 14).  
</P>
<P>
 The only acceptable rate of inflation is zero! To put this into perspective, 
think of paying 10.95% sales tax for everything you buy in Los Angeles 
County.Can you imagine the uproar which would be created if a bureaucrat asked 
the voters to approve such a level? Yet the government can get away with a 
concealed insidious tax like this and newspapers are helping brainwash the 
public that it is reasonable and acceptable. 
</P>
<P>
 This is also a tax on every dollar of savings put aside for the future. At 
this rate of inflation, every dollar saved will be worth 50 cents in 26.7 
years. 
</P>
<P>
 I beg of you not to assist the government in convincing us that anything over 
zero inflation is acceptable. This is nothing more than a hidden tax piled on 
top of our already horrendous load of taxes. 
</P>
<P>
 FRED VAN KIRK 
</P>
<P>
 Palos Verdes Estates 
</P>
</TEXT>
