<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; MISSOURI UPSETS KANSAS, TAKES LEAD IN BIG EIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Pres 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No. 3 Kansas shot only 43% and had 17 turnovers in losing to No. 20 Missouri, 
79-67, Monday night in a Big Eight game at Columbia, Mo. 
</P>
<P>
 Melvin Booker led a balanced Missouri attack with 16 points, scoring all but 
two in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tigers (15-2, 6-0) ended a six-game losing streak against the Jayhawks and 
took a two-game lead in the conference over Kansas (19-3, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 The Jayhawks have won the Big Eight regular-season championship the last three 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Woodberry scored 19 points for Kansas, which lost for the second time in 
five games. 
</P>
<P>
 Missouri has held its last 11 opponents to sub-50% shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Booker, Missouri's leading scorer with an 18.2-point average, missed all six 
of his shots in the first half. But in the second, he had three baskets and was 
six of seven at the free throw line. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly Thames and Jevon Crudup each added 14 points for Missouri. Lamont 
Frazier and Paul O'Liney had 13 apiece. OTHER GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Arturas Karnishovas made a three-point basket with 5.8 seconds left in 
overtime and Seton Hall (11-7, 4-6) overcame a second-half cold spell to record 
a 64-63 Big East victory over Providence (11-6, 4-5) at East Rutherford, N.J. 
Seton Hall made only eight baskets in the final 30 minutes but still avenged an 
earlier 24-point loss at Providence. . . . Malcolm Huckaby and Bill Curley 
keyed a 7-0 run as Boston College (16-5, 7-3) pulled away to a 71-64 Big East 
victory over Georgetown (11-6, 5-4) at Boston. Othella Harrington led the Hoyas 
with 22 points. . . . Damon Key scored 15 points and Marquette (13-5) shut down 
South Florida (9-9) for a 78-54 victory at Milwaukee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
