points to lead visiting Bakersfield (10-16, 3-0) in a WSC Northern Division 
game played at Grant High. Craig Griffin and Eric Grayson scored 12 each for 
Valley (9-15, 1-3). WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 84, Glendale 78 (OT) -- Lisa Hilton scored nine of her 18 points in 
overtime to lead Canyons in a WSC game. Glendale's Makela Theriault scored on a 
layup with eight seconds left to force the extra period. Susie Woo of Glendale 
(9-11, 5-5) led all scorers with 25 points and nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 60, Cuesta 33 -- Julie Hardy scored 15 points and Andrea Williams 
added 11 and eight steals for the visiting Pirates (20-4, 10-0) in a WSC game. 
BOYS 
</P>
<P>
 Chaminade 68, Notre Dame 66 -- Mike Yang scored on a three-foot shot with 
three seconds to play to give the Eagles the go-ahead points in a Mission 
League game. Casey Cote led Chaminade (6-12, 2-6) with 19 points and Yang added 
16 points. 
</P>
