<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: 5TH SUSPECT HELD IN SLAYING AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have arrested a fifth suspect in connection with the fatal shooting of 
a Whittier man at a Ventura motel in December, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Alfonso Serrato Cortez, 21, was taken into custody Thursday and booked into 
County Jail on suspicion of acting as an accessory to the Dec. 18 murder of 
21-year-old Paul Martinez at the Motel 6 on Johnson Drive, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cortez, of Port Hueneme, was released on $5,000 bail and is expected to be 
charged by the district attorney's office on Thursday, said Deputy Dist. Atty. 
Matthew J. Hardy, who is handling the case. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other suspects were charged with murder last Thursday, and a woman was 
charged with being an accessory to the crime for trying to help cover up the 
slaying, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
 All three murder suspects are being held in jail in lieu of $1 million bail, 
and the woman is being held on $250,000 bail, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Martinez went to Motel 6 the night of the shooting with a friend from Los 
Angeles and a group of people from Santa Paula, police said. The shooting 
occurred after an encounter with a group of people from Oxnard and Port Hueneme 
that included gang members. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities have said that at least two gunmen opened fire from inside their 
cars in the motel's parking lot. Martinez was shot and killed as he stood on 
the second-story walkway. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
