<HEADLINE>
<P>
OFF THE TICKER: IT'S JUST THE KIND OF SALE SHE'D LIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fran Menconi is putting a 20-year buying binge behind her. 
</P>
<P>
 The Tinley Park, Ill., woman, who said her spending sprees "bordered on the 
ridiculous," is cleaning out her closets and putting racks of size 12 clothes 
and accessories in a consignment store.Bargains abound: 200 pairs of earrings 
at 50 cents each, silk blouses at $15 apiece, 100 scarves and piles of other 
duds. 
</P>
<P>
 Said Menconi: "When I felt happy, I'd buy something; when I felt sad, I'd buy 
something. And sometimes I'd buy something just because my closet was such a 
mess and I couldn't find anything." 
</P>
</TEXT>
