<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Television: With Turner Broadcasting System's acquisition Friday of film 
distributor New Line Cinema, speculation is growing that cable mogul Ted 
Turner's next target may be RHI Entertainment. Led by longtime producer Robert 
Halmi Sr., RHI is one of the top suppliers of programs to the major television 
networks, including "Lonesome Dove" starring Robert Duvall and the upcoming 
"Scarlett," a miniseries sequel to "Gone With the Wind."Traders, some of whom 
are betting Turner will acquire the rest of RHI, have been quickly bidding up 
its stock. But a spokesman for RHI denies that any such plan is in the works, 
saying the company believes the stock's climb can be attributed to RHI's 
healthy earnings outlook and record backlog. RHI's stock rose 87.5 cents Monday 
to $30.125 on the American Stock Exchange. JAMES BATES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
