<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: MICHAEL JACKSON HIRES PR FIRM OF OTHER CELEBRITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Embattled pop star Michael Jackson, whose inner circle has been in a state of 
flux since summer as he has battled child molestation allegations, has added a 
new publicity firm to his camp. 
</P>
<P>
 Entertainment publicist Michael Levine confirmed that Jackson last week hired 
his Levine/Schneider firm, whose work includes public relations for such 
clients as Barbra Streisand and Jackson's sister Janet. 
</P>
<P>
 It was unclear what role longtime Jackson publicist Lee Solters will now play 
in the entertainer's career. Levine said he does not know what Solters will be 
doing. Solters said he is still working for Jackson and will remain involved in 
various matters for him. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Jackson's attorneys announced that he has settled for an 
undisclosed amount a civil lawsuit brought by a teen-age boy who accused 
Jackson of sexually molesting him. Jackson has denied the allegations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ex-Paul Kagan Associates media analyst Paul Bricault has joined the new 
media group at William Morris Agency. 
</P>
<P>
 * Arnold Rifkin, senior vice president and worldwide head of the motion 
picture division at William Morris Agency, has been named to the board of 
councilors at the USC School of Cinema-Television. 
</P>
<P>
 * Paramount Pictures has promoted Jay Rakow to senior vice president and 
general counsel. He previously was deputy general counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 * MCA's UNI Distribution Corp. has named Timothy Bixby vice president of 
finance and Carl Michelakos director of sales for special projects. Separately, 
MCA Records International has named Eamon Sherlock senior director for 
international.  
</P>
<P>
 * Columbia Pictures has promoted Stephanie Allain to senior vice president of 
production. 
</P>
<P>
 * Pamela F. Cherney has been named treasurer of MCA Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Twentieth Century Fox International announced several appointments. Scott 
Neeson was promoted to senior vice president of marketing, Doug Gleason was 
named vice president of publicity and promotion, Jim Darbinian was named vice 
president of creative advertising, and Ralph Lewis was named vice president of 
media. 
</P>
<P>
 * Barry Porter has left Bear, Stearns & Co., where he was a senior managing 
director, to join Pacific Capital Group, a merchant banking firm specializing 
in entertainment and media. 
</P>
<P>
 * Twentieth Century Fox has named Elliot Lurie executive vice president of Fox 
Music Group. 
</P>
<P>
 * Steve Plotnicki has assumed the title of president of Profile Records after 
buying out the interest of founder Cory Robbins. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nancy L. Bushkin has been promoted to director of corporate relations for 
Viacom International Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 * Susan Notarides has been promoted to executive vice president of licensing 
and merchandising at Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer, while David Bishop has been named 
executive vice president of MGM/UA Home Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Marc Brody is now vice president of eastern sales for Rysher Entertainment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
