<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tekelec Inc., a Calabasas company that had big losses last year, said Peter N. 
Vicars has resigned as president and chief executive officer and a member of 
the board of directors. Philip J. Alford, senior vice president and chief 
financial officer, has been named acting president. 
</P>
<P>
 Vicars, the company's CEO since 1987, could not be reached for comment. But 
his abrupt resignation follows the loss of $10 million for the nine months 
ended Sept. 30, in contrast with a profit of $503,000 for the same period in 
1992. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which makes diagnostic, surveillance and switching systems for 
the communications industry, in December announced a restructuring and layoff 
of 50 workers aimed at cutting overhead by $2.5 million per quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 * Barry F. Hobbs was named president and chief operating officer of AllCity 
Paging Inc. Previously, he was an executive with GTE Corp. for seven years. 
Tarzana-based AllCity is the largest independent paging company in California. 
</P>
