<P>
 There's no stopping "Mrs. Doubtfire." The Robin Williams comedy with a huge 
$172.5-million gross is now the third-highest-grossing movie released in 1993, 
after only "Jurassic Park" ($342 million) and "The Fugitive" ($179.4 
million).At the current pace of ticket sales, "Doubtfire" will catch "The 
Fugitive" by the week's end. 
</P>
<P>
 Meanwhile, "The Pelican Brief," with Julia Roberts and Denzel Washington, is 
rewriting the 1993 Top 10 list, too. With $90.3 million, it is now 1993's 
eighth-highest-grossing release, pushing "Cliffhanger," with $84 million, to 
ninth. 
