<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
SALVATION ARMY OFFERING FREE GUIDE TO QUAKE HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A guide on how to get disaster relief is available free of charge to quake 
victims and low-income individuals at Salvation Army sites throughout the 
county. 
</P>
<P>
 The 56-page guide is titled "How to Get Food, Disaster Assistance and 
Money."It is being released by the Southern California Interfaith Hunger 
Coalition in partnership with United Way of Greater Los Angeles, Comic Relief, 
Los Angeles County Department of Community and Senior Citizens Services, and 
the Federal Emergency Management Agency's Los Angeles Emergency Food and 
Shelter Program Local Board. 
</P>
<P>
 The guide is available in English and Spanish and provides information on how 
to get food, housing, health care, legal services and other benefits. It also 
provides details on assistance that is available to individuals with low 
incomes who need help throughout the year after disasters of a personal nature. 
</P>
<P>
 "Many people do not know where to turn or what help is available," said 
Elizabeth Riley, executive director of the Interfaith Hunger Coalition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
