<P>
 Avery Dennison's Business Is Steadily Improving: Profit increased in the final 
quarter and fiscal year ended Jan. 1, said the Pasadena-based maker of 
pressure-sensitive labels, tags and other office products.For the year, net 
income was $84.4 million, up 5% from $80.1 million in 1992; per-share earnings 
rose 10% to $1.46 cents a share, from $1.33 last year. Full-year sales declined 
slightly to $2.61 billion from $2.62 billion in 1992. For the fourth quarter, 
per-share earnings rose 6% to 34 cents, from 32 cents in the year-ago period; 
net income was $19.3 million, compared to $18.9 million in 1992. Sales in the 
quarter were $641.9 million, up from $629.7 million. 
</P>
