<P>
 Treasury Expected to Borrow $45 Billion: The Treasury will announce Wednesday 
how it will sell the debt for the January-March quarter, including the makeup 
of refinancing auctions to sell three- and 10-year notes and 30-year 
bonds.Borrowing projection for the current quarter, which assumed a $20-billion 
cash balance on March 31, is $15 billion to $20 billion less than the 
Treasury's Nov. 1 estimate. The earlier figure assumed a $35-billion cash 
balance on March 31. The Treasury estimated that for the April-June quarter it 
will borrow $15 billion to $20 billion. 
