<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Texaco named Lester A. Amidei Jr., 49, senior vice president of Texaco 
Refining and Marketing Inc., based in Los Angeles. He succeeds Robert C. 
Oelkers, 49, who will become comptroller of Texaco Inc. at the oil company's 
executive offices in Harrison, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles unit manufacturers and markets most Texaco petroleum products 
in the western United States.Amidei has been general manager of corporate 
planning and economics at Texaco Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 George David, president and chief operating officer of United Technologies 
Corp., has been named chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
 David replaces Robert F. Daniell, who will remain chairman of UTC's board of 
directors after David takes over as chief executive officer April 18, the 
company said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniell said he wants to focus on strategic issues for the aerospace and 
defense contractor, including international collaborations and long-term 
relationships with key government and commercial customers. 
</P>
<P>
 David, who joined the subsidiary Otis Elevator Co. in 1975, was named UTC 
president and chief operating officer in February 1992. In 1986, he was named 
chief executive officer of Otis. 
</P>
<P>
 Daniell was elected chief executive officer in 1986 and company chairman in 
1987. 
</P>
<P>
 United Technologies, based in Hartford, Conn., provides a range of 
high-technology products and support systems to the aerospace, building systems 
and automotive industries. UTC owns both Otis and Sikorsky. 
</P>
</TEXT>
