<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Infinity Reportedly Cleared to Buy KRTH-FM: The Federal Communications 
Commission today will announce that Infinity Broadcasting Corp. can proceed 
with plans to buy the big Los Angeles radio station, the New York Times 
reported in today's editions.The FCC's 2-1 vote came despite the agency's 
concern about purported indecent on-air remarks made by radio personality and 
Infinity employee Howard Stern, which also are the subject of at least two 
indecency complaints filed by the public. But the FCC's decision also levies an 
additional $400,000 in fines on Infinity, which already has been fined $1.2 
million by the commission in recent years because of Stern's comments, the 
newspaper said. Infinity is fighting the fines in court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
