TECHNOLOGY: GAME DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Among the titles that Virgin Interactive has in development is a video game 
version of "The Lion King," based on an upcoming Walt Disney Co. animated 
movie. 
</P>
<P>
 Virgin collaborated with Disney and Sega of America Inc. to create a video 
game based on the movie Aladdin. Now Alper says that cooperation, led by a 
15-person Virgin development team in Las Vegas, is being taken further in the 
Lion King project. 
</P>
<P>
 Alper says Disney tells him that the new film may top Aladdin in box-office 
receipts. If that is the case, the video game could be published this fall on 
both the Super Nintendo and Sega Genesis formats, only a few months after the 
movie's summer release. 
</P>
