<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: ODETICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The company announced Monday that it has been awarded a $1-million contract to 
manufacture a new generation of solid-state data recorders for WorldView 
Imaging Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 The recorders will be used in a WorldView satellite, scheduled to launch in 
1995, and will provide detailed images of the earth for use in mapping, 
geographic information systems, environmental planning and urban planning 
applications. WorldView is based in Livermore. 
</P>
<P>
 The Odetics recorders store information using computer memory chips, instead 
of the customary tape recording. Deliveries are scheduled to begin before the 
end of 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 Odetics, which has annual revenue of about $86 million, makes space tape 
recorders, robotic devices, automated tape libraries, data recorders and other 
automated products that store and control information. 
</P>
