<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRANSWORLD BANCORP PROFIT RISES 5% IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TransWorld Bancorp, the Sherman Oaks-based holding company for TransWorld 
Bank, said its fourth-quarter profit rose 5% to $490,000, from $467,000 in the 
same quarter a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, TransWorld posted a profit of $1.38 million, down 27% from 
$1.9 million in the previous year. TransWorld, which operates 10 branches in 
the Los Angeles area, closed 1993 with assets of $313.4 million, up 25% from 
$251.2 million at the end of 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
