<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW: 1993 HOME SALES JUMP 5% IN YEAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK SEARLES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home sales in Ventura County in 1993 showed the strongest year-to-year 
performance of any Southern California county, according to TRW REDI Property 
Data. 
</P>
<P>
 A total of 8,845 new and used residences changed hands in the county last 
year, 5% more than in 1992, the service reports. Orange County, the only other 
county in the region to register an improvement, showed a 1% gain. 
</P>
<P>
 In single-family resales, the largest part of the market, Ventura County had 
6,219 sales last year, 8% more than the previous year, according to Dataquick 
Information Systems. Condominium resales in the county last year totaled 1,403, 
a 2% decline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
